A handcrafted wooden canoe with a seperate wooden floater that is smaller than the canoe itself; placed parralel to the canoe via two wooden beams to provide stability. 

The floater enables the driver to board the canoe after leaving the rather unstable canoe in open water for diving or swimming. These types of boats are often used by socalled islanders.

Outrigger canoes van be powered by hand, via paddles, or by windforce, via a small sail and is made for single or multiple users.